Ugunja MP Opiyo Wandayi on Saturday expressed fears about the intense jostling for governor in Nyanza counties, saying it would undermine Cord leader Raila Odinga&rsquo;s chances of clinching the presidency. He said ODM will not tolerate any violence perpetuated by hopefuls or incumbents.The ODM secretary for political affairs warned the party will take severe disciplinary actions against violators. &ldquo;Contenders must know no personal sacrifices can override Raila&rsquo;s presidential bid,&rdquo; Wandayi said.He also condemned what happened in Homa Bay during the memorial of former Senator Otieno Kajwang&rsquo;, where MP Opondo Kaluma and hopeful Washington Ogaga threw punches and rolled on the ground.